   "source": [
    "# Examples of wavelet transforms\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook contains plots for a few simple time series showing them in the time (left), frequency (middle) and wavelet time-frequency (right) domains."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "0bf63705",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import WDM\n",
    "\n",
    "from WDM.code.plotting.plotting import time_domain_plot, frequency_domain_plot, time_frequency_plot"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 39,
   "id": "e56fca95",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "WDM_transform(Nf=512, N=8192, q=8, d=4, A_frac=0.25, calc_m0=True)\n",
      "self.Nt = 16 time cells\n",
      "self.Nf = 512 frequency cells\n",
      "self.dT = 512.0 time resolution\n",
      "self.dF = 0.0009765625 frequency resolution\n",
      "self.K = 8192 window length\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dt = 1.0\n",
    "N = 8192\n",
    "Nf = 512\n",
    "\n",
    "wdm = WDM.WDM.WDM_transform(dt=dt, Nf=Nf, N=N, q=8, calc_m0=True)\n",
    "print(wdm)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a7c65c4d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Low frequency sine wave."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "0d525918",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x400 with 4 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "f = lambda t, T: np.sin(2*np.pi*t/T)\n",
    "\n",
    "data = f(wdm.times, N/4)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(ncols=3, figsize=(15, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes[0] = time_domain_plot(wdm, data, figax=(fig, axes[0]))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes[1] = frequency_domain_plot(wdm, data, figax=(fig, axes[1]))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes[2] = time_frequency_plot(wdm, wdm(data), figax=(fig, axes[2]), part='real')\n",
    "axes[2].set_ylim(0, 0.008)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "daf1d713",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "High frequency sine wave"
   ]
  },

   "source": [

    "\n",
    "fig, axes[2] = time_frequency_plot(wdm, wdm(data), figax=(fig, axes[2]), part='real')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fe5e41ed",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Gaussian pulse"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "id": "386d08bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x400 with 4 Axes>"

     "output_type": "display_data"
    }

   "source": [

    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(ncols=3, figsize=(15, 4))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes[0] = time_domain_plot(wdm, data, figax=(fig, axes[0]))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes[1] = frequency_domain_plot(wdm, data, figax=(fig, axes[1]))\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes[2] = time_frequency_plot(wdm, wdm(data), figax=(fig, axes[2]), part='real')\n",
    "axes[2].set_ylim(0, 0.01)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
